.TH MYEMAIL "1" "December 2025" "myemail 202208131947-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
myemail \- Email client launcher
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B myemail
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B myemail
is a launcher script for email clients. It detects available email applications and launches the preferred client, supporting both graphical and console-based email applications.
.PP
The script provides a unified interface for accessing email regardless of which client is installed on the system.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-console
Use console-based email applications (mutt, neomutt, etc.)
.TP
.BR \-\-term
Open the email client in a terminal window with a menu
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B myemail
Launch the default email client
.TP
.B myemail --console
Launch console-based email client (mutt/neomutt)
.TP
.B myemail --term
Open email client in a new terminal window
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/myemail/settings.conf
User configuration file for myemail preferences
.TP
.B ~/.local/log/myemail/
Log file directory for error tracking
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MYEMAIL_CLIENT
Override the default email client selection
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
No email client found
